\section*{EXPERIENCE}
\WorkExperience{SOFTWARE ENGINEER \hfill UK, Remote}{OpenZeppelin \hfill 2023 {-} 2026} \\
\Skills{TypeScript, React, Next.js, Solidity, Rust, Claude, Cursor, Playwright, Jest, Cypress, PostgreSQL, Redis, AWS, Kubernetes, Docker, Terraform}
\begin{itemize}
	\item Co-led \textbf{Defender 2.0 Secure Audit} as one of two engineers, working closely with smart contract auditors and clients to plan, prioritize, and ship TypeScript and React workflows for findings, fix verification, and final PDF reports.
	\item Shaped \textbf{audit-facing workflows} around findings, remediation status, fix verification, and report delivery, making complex security work easier for auditors and client teams to follow.
	\item Supported the Defender sunset by closing feature gaps, improving documentation, and \textbf{working directly with enterprise users} during migration to OSS Relayer, which covered most enterprise Defender users.
	\item Owned the \textbf{EVM side of Relayer OSS}, including transaction cost handling, RPC balancing, retry and failover logic, AWS KMS and GCP KMS signer integrations, and a fix for a critical nonce race condition.
	\item Refactored the TypeScript monorepo build system, \textbf{reducing builds from 15 to 3 minutes} in local and CI runs.
	\item Cut alert noise by about 60\% across Slack and PagerDuty by tuning recoverable RPC and gas-spike alerts.
\end{itemize}

